The given expression is $$\frac{(y-x)^2}{(y-z)(z-x)} + \frac{(z-y)^2}{(z-x)(x-y)} + \frac{(x-z)^2}{(x-y)(y-z)}.$$ 
To simplify the expression, we can put everything over a common denominator. The common denominator will be $(y-z)(z-x)(x-y)$.

